description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 14, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope today: Read your astrological predictions

description: Haryana CM Nayab Singh Saini is set to continue, with endorsement from PM Modi and Amit Shah. Despite demands from Union minister Rao Inderjit Singh, Shah and Madhya Pradesh CM Mohan Yadav will oversee the BJP legislature party meeting to elect the CM. Meanwhile, J&K prepares for a government led by Omar Abdullah of the National Conference.
title: Amit Shah, Mohan Yadav to be observers for Haryana CM pick

description: In response to Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge's comment labeling BJP as a 'party of terrorists,' BJP president J P Nadda criticized Congress for ideological bankruptcy, highlighting its electoral failures and alleged support for anti-national forces. Nadda also suggested Kharge introspect on the party's declining public trust.
title: Maliikarjun Kharge's 'terrorist' jibe at BJP sign of Congress desperation: JP Nadda

description: Rahul Gandhi has urged PM Modi and Defence Minister Rajnath Singh to address the unequal treatment of deceased Agniveers compared to other martyred soldiers. Following the deaths of Agniveers Gohil Vishwaraj Singh and Saifat Sheet during training in Nashik, Gandhi questions why their families won't receive equivalent compensation, pension, and other government benefits.
title: Rahul Gandhi attacks government after death of 2 Agniveers

description: Police are probing multiple angles in the murder of ex-minister Baba Siddique, including disputes over Slum Rehabilitation Authority projects. Siddique, previously investigated by the ED for his role in the Jamaat-e-Jamhooria slums project, had faced allegations of fraud involving forged documents and fictitious slum dwellers, drawing increased scrutiny from authorities.
title: Baba Siddique murder case: Slum dispute that sparked ED inquest to be part of probe

description: Two men accused in the Gauri Lankesh murder case received a hero's welcome in Vijayapura, Karnataka, after being granted bail following seven years in jail. Sri Ram Sene members honored Parashuram Waghmore and Manohar Yadawe, who later performed religious rituals and avoided media interaction.
title: Clip of hero's welcome for 2 accused of killing Lankesh goes viral

description: The motive behind the murder of former Maharashtra MLA Ziauddin Siddique remains uncertain after the arrest of two shooters and their handler. Links to the Lawrence Bishnoi gang and a possible dispute over a slum rehabilitation project are being investigated by Mumbai Police.
title: Baba Siddique case: One of the killers established links with Bishnoi gang in jail

description: Saturday's killing of NCP functionary Baba Siddique in Mumbai resembles the murders of UP gangsters Atiq Ahmed and Ashraf, and Sanjeev Maheshwari. Unknown shooters with limited criminal histories were contracted by hidden players, using sophisticated weapons to execute high-profile killings with precision.
title: Baba Siddique case: UP saw similar murders of gangsters Atiq, Ashraf Ahmed

description: Baba Siddique, a Bandra politician known for his helpful nature and civic work, was admired for his dedication to social causes and inclusiveness. He supported many community initiatives and frequently attended and contributed to local events. Siddique's generosity and accessibility to people, regardless of their background, gained him widespread respect.
title: Baba Siddique murder: Residents mourn Bandra boy, a go-getter with a heart of gold

description: The suspect has been identified as Vem Miller who was carrying a fake press card and entry pass. He is believed to be a member of a rightwing anti-government organization and was plotting to kill Trump, the Sheriff said. "They were different enough to cause the deputies alarm," Bianco said.
title: Third assassination attempt on Donald Trump? Armed man arrested from Coachella

description: India's GJEPC has adopted new standards for defining a diamond, now requiring it to refer only to natural stones mined from the earth. This move aligns with the USA's FTC guidelines and aims to prevent lab-grown diamonds from being misrepresented. GJEPC is urging updates to the Consumer Protection Act to reflect this definition.
title: Diamond is mined stone, not lab-grown, says gems trade body

description: Four youths died and two sustained serious injuries after an unknown vehicle hit two motorbikes on SH-78 in Nalanda district, Bihar, on Saturday night. The victims were returning from a Dussehra fair. Police are investigating to identify the vehicle responsible.
title: 4 killed as 'unknown' vehicle rams into 2 bikes in Nalanda

description: The Global University Association Forum's third meeting in Beijing prioritized AI in education, academic equivalence for global mobility, and sustainable campuses. Expanding higher education to STEAM was emphasized. India will host the fourth conference in 2025. Agreements for research collaboration were signed between universities from India and China, aimed at providing a global platform for students.
title: STEM to STEAM: Global forum eyes higher education focus on arts too

description: BENGALURU: A 22-year-old woman and her 30-year-old lover have been arrested for allegedly killing her two young sons, aged 2 years and 11 months, in Ramanagara district. The infants were viewed as obstacles to their illicit relationship. Suspicious behavior at a graveyard led to their arrest.
title: Disturbed by their screams, woman, lover kill her 2 sons

description: Enforcement Directorate has begun returning lost funds to nearly six crore investors targeted by the Rs 50,000 crore Pearl Group ponzi scam. It shared details of Rs 700 crore worth of attached assets with the Lodha Committee for victim restitution. Investigations revealed funds siphoned off internationally, leading to multiple property attachments, including assets in Australia and India.
title: Refund drive starts for 6cr investors in Rs 50,000 crore ponzi case

description: Rajesh Kumar, a wanted criminal involved in over 50 cases, including murder and extortion, was killed in a police encounter in Meerut. Kumar, who fired at the police, was injured and later died in the hospital. Another incident in Khurja saw the arrest of two men for the murder of an Armyman earlier this month.
title: Man wanted in over 50 cases gunned down in UP encounter

description: Authorities will systematically verify 'high-risk' income tax refund claims for the 2024-25 assessment year, following a standard operating procedure. Cases involving suspicious patterns, such as false deductions or expenses, will be investigated to ensure claims are legitimate, emphasizing non-harassment of genuine taxpayers.
title: 'High-risk' income tax refund claims under scanner

description: Foreign portfolio investors have sold Rs 58,711 crore ($7 billion) of Indian equities in Oct, influenced by China's economic stimulus. Net bond sales were modest at Rs 709 crore. However, strong domestic institutional investments mitigated the market impact. FPIs have also shown interest in Hyundai's upcoming IPO.
title: FPIs pull out Rs 59,000 crore from equity in October

description: CCPA directs Ola to offer an option for refunds either as a bank transfer or a coupon, identifying existing practices as unfair. Ola is also mandated to provide receipts for auto rides and address key consumer complaints. Policy changes including clear grievance contact details, cancellation policies, and fare breakdowns have been implemented.
title: Offer refund choice to users: Consumer panel to cab company

description: In Bahraich, an FIR has been lodged against Salman, while 20-30 individuals are detained following a violent clash. SP Vrinda Shukla confirmed that police are investigating the incident and monitoring the idol immersion process to ensure order. Special teams are deployed, and videos are being recorded for evidence.
title: Tensions ease in Maharajganj after clash, FIR filed; police take action to ensure smooth idol immersion

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge's family-run trust withdrew a request for a five-acre site in Bengaluru's Aerospace Park for a multi-skill development centre, following BJP's allegations of favoritism and an ongoing investigation. The family cited politically motivated allegations as the reason for their decision.
title: Kharge's family trust recalls land plea amid Siddaramaiah wife's plot row

description: Police in Manipur arrested two PREPAK members involved in extorting businesses in Imphal West. Seized were mobile phones, a motorbike, and a driving licence. The anti-extortion unit led by additional DGP includes 15 crack teams targeting increased extortion activities since May 3 last year.
title: Anti-extortion drive nets two banned Manipur outfit members

description: Nanda Anand Asande works for Shri Mahila Griha Udyog Lijjat Papad, a women-led cooperative producing Lijjat papad, among other snacks. Founded in 1959, the organization operates across India, empowering 45,000 women. Members like Asande roll papads at home, earning around Rs 10,000 monthly, which allows them to support their families and achieve self-reliance.
title: Kneading hope into women through co-op work, Lijjat turns 65

description: The Indian Medical Association announces a nationwide hunger strike on Oct 15, supporting West Bengal junior doctors' fast-unto-death agitation over the rape and murder of a colleague. The movement gains widespread support as the doctors' condition worsens, with ex-students and medical associations joining in solidarity.
title: IMA to hold hunger strike in solidarity with RG Kar doctors

description: The Andhra Pradesh government has transferred the investigation into the 2021 attacks on TDP's headquarters and the residence of CM N Chandrababu Naidu to the CID, as previous police efforts were deemed slow. CID will start examining the case, involving allegations against YSRCP functionaries, on Monday.
title: CID to probe 2021 attack on Chandrababu Naidu office, home

description: Roopkund Lake in Uttarakhand is shrinking due to climate change, with forest officials and scientists attributing the reduction in size to altered precipitation patterns. The shift from snow to rain is causing moraine to slide into the lake, reducing its volume and area.
title: Concern grows as Uttarakhand's 'skeleton lake' is shrinking

description: High food inflation in India is driven by volatile tomato, onion, and potato prices due to short crop cycles, storage issues, and extreme weather. An RBI working paper suggests reforms like private mandis, re-launching futures trading, and expanding cold storage facilities to stabilize prices and support farmers.
title: Explained: How tomato, potato, onion influence food inflation

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar is expected to visit Pakistan on Oct 15-16 for the SCO heads of govt meeting, marking the first Indian foreign minister visit in a decade. No formal bilateral meetings are planned; focus on terrorism and regional security is anticipated.
title: SCO meet: EAM Jaishankar to be in Pakistan tomorrow, attend Shehbaz Sharif dinner

description: India commissions its second nuclear-powered submarine, INS Arighaat, and sets up a new VLF transmitting station for secure communication with submarines. This facility, along with upcoming SSBNs and SSNs, aims to bolster India's naval capabilities amid increasing Chinese activity in the Indian Ocean.
title: Navy sets up base to control submarines on long-range patrols
30 hospitalized due to food poisoning at Varkala

description: Two coaches of an unoccupied local train derailed while entering a car shed from Mumbai Central, impacting Western Railway services. No injuries were reported. Trains were rerouted to the fast line, and technical teams expedited clearing the track. A thorough investigation will be conducted to prevent future incidents.
title: Derailment of Western Rail local’s coach affects train service; no injuries

description: Iran is facing a critical cyberattack wave disrupting its government and infrastructure, notably affecting nuclear facilities.
title: Iran hit by cyberattacks; 'nuclear facilities & govt agencies targeted'
US to send anti-missile system, troops to Israel amid conflict with Iran

description: A Chandigarh resident won a consumer court case against Amazon for fraudulent transactions. The court ordered Amazon to refund Rs 40,325 and pay Rs 18,000 in compensation and litigation costs.
title: Amazon fined for not refunding Rs 40k to woman whose phone was 'hacked'

description: India's captain Harmanpreet Kaur scored an unbeaten 54, but the team fell short by nine runs against Australia in the women's T20 World Cup. With the defeat, India's semifinal chance now depends on the result of New Zealand's match against Pakistan.
title: T20 World Cup: India on the brink after narrow loss to Aus

description: India's chances for a Women's T20 World Cup semifinal spot dimmed after a nine-run defeat to Australia. Despite finishing second in Group A, India's progression depends on Pakistan beating New Zealand in Monday's match. A Pakistan win would advance India on net run rate, while a New Zealand victory would secure the last semifinal spot for them.
title: Why India need Pakistan win over NZ to secure semifinal berth

description: AAP chief Arvind Kejriwal advises Omar Abdullah on handling limited CM powers in J&K, likening it to Delhi's constraints. Kejriwal welcomes AAP's first electoral win in J&K and hopes Mehraj Malik gains a ministerial role. He criticizes BJP for not providing free electricity and improving public services despite ruling in 22 states.
title: Omar can consult me if he faces trouble running a 'half-state': Kejriwal

description: President's rule in Jammu and Kashmir has been revoked paving the way for a new government formation in the union territory. The Union home ministry issued the notification following Omar Abdullah's meeting with the lieutenant governor to stake claim after the recent assembly elections. This change ends the central rule in place since June 2017, post-BJP withdrawal from Mehbooba Mufti's coalition government.
title: President's rule revoked in J&K after almost 6 years, stage set for Omar Abdullah's government

description: A court has ordered an ossification test for Dharamraj Kashayap, accused in the murder of NCP leader Baba Siddique, due to conflicting age claims. Kashayap claims he is 17, while his Aadhaar indicates he is 19. The Supreme Court has acknowledged the test's utility but noted its margin of error and non-conclusiveness.
title: Baba Siddiqui murder: Why court ordered ossification test for 2nd accused

description: In a major development in the murder case of Senior Nationalist Congress Party (NCP) leader Baba Siddique, police have arrested the third suspect, Pravin Lonkar. The 28-year-old was apprehended in Pune and is the brother of Shubham Lonkar, who is also implicated in the conspiracy. The Lonkar brothers allegedly enlisted Dharmaraj Kashyap and Shivkumar Gautam in the plot to kill Siddique. Investigations are ongoing as authorities continue to gather evidence, a police official informed.
title: Baba Siddique murder case: Police arrest third accused in Pune

description: North Korea ordered artillery units to be on standby to open fire, claiming South Korean drones carried propaganda leaflets into Pyongyang's airspace. The North's officials labeled these flights as a military attack and a grave provocation, leading to heightened military alertness on both sides.
title: North Korea orders border army to 'get fully ready to open fire'

description: Delhi and Gujarat Police on Sunday seized 518 kilograms of cocaine worth Rs 5,000 crore as part of a zero-tolerance drug policy. This follows a previous bust involving 562 kilograms of cocaine and 40 kilograms of hydroponic marijuana. Police also arrested four associates of inter-state drug kingpin Shahi Mahatma in Shimla.
title: Delhi & Gujarat police seize 518 kg of cocaine worth Rs 5k cr in joint op

description: Hamas leaders, including Yahya Sinwar, spent over two years planning an attack on Israel, revealed in documents obtained by The New York Times. They sought involvement from Iran and Hezbollah. The attack, initially planned for 2022, aimed to disrupt Israel's normalisation with Saudi Arabia and assert control over regional disputes.
title: The secret strategy behind Hamas' surprise attack on Israel on Oct 7

description: Rahul Kharge, son of Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge, withdrew his request for a 5-acre land allotment in Bengaluru intended for a skill development center, citing political motivations. This follows scrutiny and allegations of nepotism and misuse of power by BJP members.
title: Kharge's son withdraws B'luru land allotment request amid 'nepotism' charges

description: A 19-year-old Delhi University student from Manipur accused the police of leniently handling her harassment complaint against a cab driver who held her hostage with intent to rape. Despite filing an FIR, minor charges allowed the culprit to easy bail. She criticised the police for their delayed and indifferent response. The student urges the police to ensure safety, pointing out discrepancies in the cab driver's identity.
title: DU student decries police for offering cab driver 'easy path to bail'

description: A man's evening walk in Chicago took a gruesome turn when he discovered a human head in a box on West Taylor Street, mistaking it initially for a Halloween prop. Police and the Cook County Medical Examiner’s Office are investigating, with autopsy results pending. Authorities are also probing another case of skeletal remains found near the Kennedy Expressway in Bucktown.
title: Human head found in a box on Chicago street; investigation underway

description: Top American general calls Trump a 'total fascist' and 'most dangerous person ever,' while Trump critics’ relentless attacks strengthen his support. Trump's derogatory remarks and scandals incite backlash, but polling shows no significant shift in voter support. Revenge themes dominate Trump's campaign rhetoric.
title: Fart of the deal: Mark and Mary fail to move MAGA devout from 'Diaper Don'

description: A bomb threat was found on a Chennai-bound Indigo flight with 169 passengers, including a minister and a judge. The flight took off around 6pm after thorough checks by CISF. This followed an Air India Express flight incident in Trichy due to a hydraulic snag.
title: Bomb threat letter found on Chennai-bound flight, minister, HC judge aboard

description: Senior Nationalist Congress Party (NCP) leader Baba Siddique tragically passed away on Saturday after being shot multiple times by unidentified assailants. On Sunday, several Bollywood celebrities, including Salman Khan, gathered at Baba Siddique's house to pay their last respects amid heavy security. Stars such as Shehnaaz Gill, Raj Kundra, Giorgia Andriani, Ramesh Taurani, Maniesh Paul, Urvashi Rautela, Rashami Desai, and Zareen Khan were also seen offering their condolences.
title: Baba Siddique funeral: After Salman Khan, these celebs pay respects
In a surprise Sunday visit, PM Modi visits PM GatiShakti Anubhuti Kendra
Baba Siddiqui case: Accused on the run flaunted 'gangster' status on Instagram
'Fighter, advocate of the oppressed': Politicians, family mourn GN Saibaba

description: The FBI created an Ethereum-based token, NexFundAI, to uncover market manipulation in cryptocurrency trading. The sting operation resulted in charges against 30 individuals and entities, revealing fraudulent practices like wash trades by market makers and other defendants. $25 million in fraudulent proceeds will be returned to investors.
title: Why FBI built crypto coin of its own to enter cryptocurrency industry

description: Former Pakistan captain Younis Khan criticizes current Test skipper Shan Masood's leadership qualities, suggesting he was appointed for his communication skills rather than his abilities. Babar Azam is dropped for the next tests against England due to poor form, while key bowlers Shaheen Shah Afridi and Naseem Shah are rested.
title: 'English, Urdu achhi bolta hai': Younis takes indirect jibe at Masood

description: SpaceX conducted a high-stakes test flight of its 400-foot Starship rocket, attempting to recover the first-stage booster with mechanical arms at the launch pad. After launch from Texas, the booster aimed for a return to the pad, while the spacecraft planned a splashdown in the Indian Ocean. Enhancements were made to software and the heat shield.
title: SpaceX’s Starship makes history with first-ever launch pad catch

description: Indonesia has requested Google and Apple to block the Chinese app Temu to protect local small and medium businesses.
title: Why this country has asked Google and Apple to block China's Temu

description: Solainne Moncero-Tannis sues A Haunting in Hollis after breaking both ankles on a 20-foot slide. The haunted house has been shut down due to safety violations, including structural and electrical issues. This marks the fifth lawsuit against the attraction for injuries.
title: Woman sues haunted house after breaking both ankles at the tourist attraction

description: Pakistan lost by an innings and 47 runs to England in the first Test in Multan, leading to heavy criticism. Ex-England captain Michael Vaughan called this the worst Pakistan team he's seen. Changes for the second Test include dropping Babar Azam and pace bowlers Shaheen Afridi and Naseem Shah.
title: 'This is the worst Pakistan side': Michael Vaughan

description: Former head coach Rahul Dravid reunited with Indian cricket stalwarts Rohit Sharma, Rishabh Pant, and Virat Kohli at the Chinnaswamy Stadium ahead of their first Test against New Zealand. Dravid's presence brought added motivation to the team. The series serves as important preparation for the upcoming five-match Test series against Australia.
title: Watch: Dravid reunites with Rohit & Kohli ahead of first NZ Test

description: The mothers of two young men arrested for the murder of NCP leader Baba Siddique claim minimal contact with their sons. Both accused, aged 23 and 19, were working in a scrapyard in Pune. The Mumbai Police arrested them shortly after the incident, recovering 28 live cartridges. The suspects are now in police custody.
title: 'Came home in Holi ... ': What mothers of Baba Siddique murder accused said

description: Gurmel, linked to Kaithal, Haryana, is a key suspect in Mumbai's Baba Siddique murder case. Released on bail for a 2019 murder, he moved to Mumbai and connected with Lawrence Bishnoi's associates. Gurmel's criminal history includes multiple cases, and his grandmother expresses disownment. Mumbai Crime Branch teams are actively investigating.
title: Baba Siddique murder: Out on bail in murder case, accused Gurmel has Bishnoi gang connection

description: The Kerala government implemented a Virtual Queue system for the Sabarimala pilgrimage, eliminating spot booking to ensure smooth and safe operations. The system allows online booking of darshan tickets and prasadam, with a daily cap of 80,000 pilgrims. The decision faces opposition from local political parties.
title: Sabarimala Darshan: What is Virtual queue system that BJP is opposing

description: Former Sri Lanka cricketer Mahela Jayawardene returns as Mumbai Indians head coach, having previously served from 2017 to 2022 before taking on the Global Head of Cricket role. Jayawardene sees this as an exciting challenge to further the franchise's success, enhance MI's legacy, and build on the vision set by the team owners.
title: Jayawardene returns as Mumbai Indians head coach

description: Authorities in Detroit have released doorbell footage showing two suspects posing as energy workers, before allegedly killing 72-year-old jewelry store owner Hussein Murray in his home. The suspects, wearing high-visibility vests and face masks, are being sought, with one already apprehended in Louisiana.
title: Video: Murder suspects disguise as energy workers before killing jewelry store owner
Refund via bank account or coupon: Ola asked to provide mode choice to consumers

description: ​Anti-monarchy campaign group Republic has hit out at the Royal Family and said if politicians are expected to display higher standards by mandatory disclosure of gifts, the same should be demanded from the royals as well. Graham Smith, chief executive of Republic, said: “If politicians are being lambasted for failing to declare gifts, the same should apply to the royals.
title: Why King Charles has not disclosed list of gifts Royal Family got since 2020

description: Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal expressed hope that Mehraj Malik will get a role in Omar Abdullah's government in Jammu and Kashmir in exchange of AAP's full support. "Since AAP has supported the Omar Abdullah government, I hope that our Mehraj Malik (AAP MLA) will be given responsibility in Omar Abdullah's government, so that he can serve the entire Jammu and Kashmir along with Doda," he said.
title: 'Since AAP supported ... ': What Kejriwal wants from Omar Abdullah in J&K

description: Pakistan's Fakhar Zaman supports Babar Azam, arguing against dropping him due to poor form. Fakhar highlights that India supported Virat Kohli during his slump. After Pakistan's opening Test defeat to England, changes include Shaheen Afridi and Naseem Shah being sidelined, with a new selection panel installed.
title: 'India didn't bench Kohli': Fakhar hits out at PCB over Babar's omission

description: Scammers are exploiting Microsoft’s reputation by sending fake emails that mimic official communications, often containing malicious links or fake login pages. These sophisticated phishing attempts can lead to account takeovers and data theft. How can users and businesses stay safe? By awareness training, AI-powered email security and quick software patching.
title: Why you should be careful of emails from ‘Microsoft employees’

description: Former Pakistan captain Babar Azam, star pacers Shaheen Afridi and Naseem Shah were dropped from the Pakistan squad for the upcoming Tests against England. The decision comes after Pakistan's heavy innings defeat in the first Test. Selectors cited the need for rest to regain fitness and confidence. Shan Masood retains his spot as captain while new players have been included in the side.
title: Pakistan drop Babar, Shaheen for 2nd & 3rd Tests vs England

description: The Maha Vikas Aghadi (MVA) alliance criticized the Maharashtra government for poor law and order, alleged corruption, and unfulfilled promises. Uddhav Thackeray emphasized BJP's reliance on dubious leaders, while the opposition released a booklet accusing the government of betraying the state for Gujarat. Upcoming assembly elections are anticipated.
title: 'Let Mahayuti announce ... ': What Uddhav said on MVA's CM face in Maharashtra

description: Rising star Washington Sundar won the 'Impact Fielder' Award for his exceptional performance in the T20I series against Bangladesh, beating Hardik Pandya and Riyan Parag. His three catches and tight economy rate were pivotal. Coach T Dilip lauded the team's collective spirit. India will face New Zealand in a three-Test home series next.
title: Washington outclasses Pandya, Parag to win...

description: Former Maharashtra minister Baba Siddique was shot dead outside his son's Mumbai office, with the Lawrence Bishnoi gang claiming responsibility. Three shooters were involved, two of whom—Gurmail Baljit Singh and Dharamraj Kashyap—are arrested, while the third, Shiv Kumar, remains at large. A handler is also on the run, and the incident occurred around 9:30 pm.
title: 'Didn't want war but ... ': Post links Bishnoi gang to Baba Siddique's murder

description: The Indian Computer Emergency Response Team (CERT-In) has issued a 'High' severity warning for Android users, citing multiple vulnerabilities in Android versions 12 through 15.
title: Government has ‘high risk’ warning for these Android users

description: Chinese surveillance camera maker Hikvision is reportedly downsizing its R&D department amid US sanctions and economic pressures. Over 1,000 employees in China could be affected. Hikvision denies large-scale layoffs, claiming internal adjustments to optimize R&D efficiency while navigating global challenges and market restrictions.
title: Chinese surveillance camera maker Hikvision may cut 1000 jobs

description: Open communication and emotional connections are emphasized for all signs this week, enhancing both relationships and possibilities for singles. Honest conversations, shared activities, and respecting personal space will strengthen bonds. Trust, patience, and understanding are crucial for nurturing relationships and attracting meaningful connections.
title: Weekly Love Horoscope, October 13 to October 19, 2024: Read your weekly astrological romantic predictions for all zodiac signs

description: The push for Bhojpuri to gain 'official language' status has intensified, with Mahagathbandhan leaders committing to raise the issue in Parliament. Inspired by the recent inclusion of other languages in the Eighth Schedule of the Constitution, they argue for central government action to support Bhojpuri's significant regional presence.
title: Mahagathbandhan renews call for 'official language' status for Bhojpuri

description: Following the murder of former Maharashtra minister Baba Siddique in Mumbai, political tensions have risen. The BJP government is urging against politicizing the incident, while Rahul Gandhi criticizes them for a law and order collapse. The police have arrested two suspects, and the search for a third is ongoing.
title: BJP and Congress lock horns after Baba Siddique shot dead in Mumbai

description: Over 100 children in Karachi, Pakistan, have died this year due to diphtheria, primarily because of the absence of Diphtheria Anti-Toxin (DAT). Despite the availability of vaccines, the critical antitoxin’s shortage has resulted in numerous fatalities, stressing the need for timely vaccination and sufficient medical resources.
title: Over 100 children die in Pak from diphtheria amid shortage of Antitoxin

description: Baba Siddique, a former Maharashtra minister and NCP leader, was shot dead near Colgate Ground in Mumbai. Two of the accused have been arrested, while one remains at large. Siddique had recently joined NCP after resigning from Congress in February 2024.
title: Baba Siddique’s last Instagram post: 'End of .....'

description: Mary Trump criticized her uncle, Donald Trump, and Elon Musk for undermining American democracy. She accused them of selling influence, with Musk financially backing Trump's campaign by paying voters in swing states to support certain amendments. Mary argued this dangerous alliance with figures like Putin threatens US interests and democratic values.
title: 'Always been for sale': Trump's niece says Musk is 'new owner' of her uncle

description: During the third T20I against Bangladesh in Hyderabad, India's allrounder Hardik Pandya won hearts by taking photos with a ball boy despite being in the middle of the match. India, led by Suryakumar Yadav, defeated Bangladesh by 133 runs, completing a 3-0 series sweep.
title: Hardik Pandya clicks selfie with ball boy mid-match

description: Former cricketer Aakash Chopra lauded Hardik Pandya's exceptional performance in India's T20I series against Bangladesh, highlighting his crucial role in the third match where he scored 47 runs off 18 balls. Chopra noted Pandya's remarkable comeback, maintaining a strike rate above 200 across all matches, and praised his aggressive batting style and confidence.
title: 'He has seen the lows of lows': Ex-India player praises 'sensational' Hardik

description: The Delhi government has resumed its campaign to remove end-of-life vehicles, impounding 213 vehicles recently. ELVs, defined as diesel vehicles over 10 years old and petrol vehicles over 15, are being targeted to reduce pollution. The initiative aims to send these vehicles to registered scrapping facilities for proper disposal.
title: Delhi govt resumes crackdown on end-of-life vehicles after 8 months

description: Former Maharashtra minister Baba Siddique was shot dead outside his son's office in Kher Nagar, Mumbai, on Dussehra evening. The assailants, three unknown men, attacked him around 9.30 pm; two have been detained, and one is on the run. Police suspect possible links to a Slum Rehabilitation Authority dispute and the Lawrence Bishnoi gang.
title: Baba Siddique’s last post on social media: 'Happiness, peace and prosperity...'

description: Vast, a space tech company, reveals design for Haven-1, the world's first commercial space station. Launching on SpaceX's Falcon 9 rocket in 2025, it features luxury amenities like a state-of-the-art gym, private rooms, and an observation window, aiming to welcome visitors by 2026.  With extraordinary lavish features, Haven-1 aims to redefine space travels.
title: Haven-1: A glimpse into the world’s first resort-like commercial space station

description: Qualcomm CEO Cristiano R. Amon honored late Ratan Tata, lauding his transformative leadership of Tata Group. Amon highlighted Tata's lasting impact on global industries and their shared values of innovation and integrity. He also underscored recent Tata-Qualcomm collaborations in technology, reinforcing the Digital India initiative. The tribute aims to inspire and acknowledge profound contributions.
title: Qualcomm CEO pays tribute to Ratan Tata: “On behalf of Qualcomm, I extend our …”

description: India's crucial ICC Women’s T20 World Cup clash against Australia will focus on improving net run rate and solidifying semifinal chances. Shafali Verma emphasizes the team's awareness of NRR. India need a win against the unbeaten Australians to match their points. Australia's injury concerns add intrigue to this high-stakes showdown in Sharjah.
title: 'We have NRR in our minds': Shafali ahead of must-win match vs Australia

description: Pakistan is set to drop star batsman Babar Azam for the second Test against England starting October 15, following an innings defeat in Multan. The decision, recommended by the new selection committee, comes after Babar's prolonged poor form in Test cricket, averaging under 21 in nine Tests this year. Since the start of 2023, Babar averages under 21 in nine Tests.
title: Pakistan set to drop Babar Azam

description: Rajya Sabha MP Kapil Sibal challenged RSS Chief Mohan Bhagwat's emphasis on social harmony, doubting if leaders like Modi are listening. In his Vijayadashmi speech, Bhagwat stressed unity amid diverse languages and cultures, while warning against threats like 'Wokeism' and 'Cultural Marxists' targeting societal values. Congress leader Mallikarjun Kharge also criticized Bhagwat's stance.
title: 'Who is listening? Modi?': Kapil Sibal on RSS chief Bhagwat's remarks

description: India achieved a decisive 133-run victory over Bangladesh in Hyderabad, scoring 297 runs, the second highest in men's T20 Internationals. Sanju Samson and Suryakumar Yadav's explosive 173-run partnership played a crucial role. India completed a 3-0 series sweep, following previous wins in New Delhi and Gwalior.
title: Bangladesh team's 'SOS call to Hyd Police' & other viral memes after India wins 3rd T20

description: In December 2004 during India's tour to Bangladesh, Sachin Tendulkar and Anil Kumble had a humorous run-out incident in the 1st Test at Dhaka. Their miscommunication resulted in both players ending up at the same end, leading to a comical but non-dismissal event, lightening the match's mood. After all the confusion and hilarious running between the wickets, Kumble was adjudged not out and it was signaled two leg byes.
title: When Sachin Tendulkar and Anil Kumble's running left everyone in splits

description: Baba Siddique, a former Maharashtra minister, was shot and killed in Mumbai. He was attacked by three unidentified assailants outside his son's office.  Riteish Deshmukh has expressed his sorrow on X, stating, “Extremely saddened and shocked beyond words to learn about the tragic demise of Shri #BabaSiddique ji. My heart goes out to @zeeshan_iyc and the entire family..."
title: Mourning Riteish Deshmukh calls for justice after Baba Siddique's death

description: Heavy rains have caused significant waterlogging in Madurai and surrounding districts, leading to a vehicle rescue operation after it was submerged in floodwaters. The IMD has downgraded the alert to yellow for South Tamil Nadu but predicts more heavy rain and strong winds in isolated areas. Fishermen are advised to avoid the sea during this period.
title: Watch: 3 rescued from submerged vehicle amid heavy rains in Madurai

description: Skipper Suryakumar Yadav rested Arshdeep Singh, bringing in Mayank Yadav, who impressed in his debut by taking two crucial wickets in India's third T20I win against Bangladesh. Mayank's consistent performance throughout the series earned him praise from the team and coach Gautam Gambhir. India's next T20I assignment will begin on November 8, with India touring South Africa for a four-match series.
title: Suryakumar hands trophy to Mayank, Gambhir reacts

description: Former Maharashtra minister Baba Siddique was shot dead outside his son's office in Mumbai. Police are investigating possible motives, including contract killing and business rivalry. Two suspects from Uttar Pradesh and Haryana are in custody, while a third is on the run. The incident has sparked concerns over law and order ahead of state elections.
title: Accused had done recce of Baba Siddique's house: What we know so far

description: NCP leader Baba Siddique succumbed to gunshot wounds after being admitted to Mumbai's Lilavati Hospital. Despite extensive resuscitation efforts, he was declared dead at 11.27 pm. Police have arrested two suspects and recovered the weapon used in the shooting. Siddique, a three-time MLA, was shot in Nirmal Nagar on Saturday evening.
title: What Lilavati Hospital doctors said after Baba Siddique’s death

description: Rahul Gandhi criticizes Maharashtra government following the death of NCP leader Baba Siddique, who was shot by assailants. Gandhi calls for responsibility and justice, highlighting a collapse in law and order. Two suspects from Haryana and UP have been arrested by Mumbai Police.
title: 'Horrifying, complete collapse of law and order': Rahul on Baba Siddique murder

description: Union minister Pralhad Joshi countered Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge's remarks about BJP, highlighting past terror incidents under UPA rule and accusing Congress of being lenient on terror convicts. He emphasized the decline in terrorist activities under PM Narendra Modi's leadership and criticized Kharge for his comments, urging him to double-check his statements.
title: 'Sonia Gandhi shed tears for terrorists': BJP's Pralhad Joshi on Kharge's remarks

description: Hardik Pandya attributed India’s 3-0 T20I series win over Bangladesh to the positive environment fostered by skipper Suryakumar Yadav and coach Gautam Gambhir. Pandya highlighted the freedom and enjoyment in the team, which led to standout performances, including Sanju Samson’s maiden T20I century and Pandya’s consistent all-round contributions throughout the series.
title: 'Feel like doing more': Hardik on his performance vs Bangladesh

description: In Madhya Pradesh's Vidisha district, a village named Ravan Panchayat celebrated Dussehra by worshipping a 500-year-old lying idol of Ravana, referred to as 'Ravan Baba.' The deity, considered the First God or 'Kul Devta,' is given the first wedding invitation and involved in annual rituals and feasts.
title: For 500 years, this village in MP worships Ravan as ‘Kul Devta’

description: The Haryana assembly election result stunned Congress, reminiscent of their shock defeat in Punjab in 2012. Captain Amarinder Singh's overconfidence was blamed for the loss back then. Despite a strong standing before the 2022 Punjab elections, internal mismanagement led to their worst performance. Now, Congress must introspect and reorganize to regain voter trust.
title: Déjà vu for Congress: A Punjab 2012 story in Haryana results

description: India triumphed over Bangladesh in the third T20I with a 133-run victory, clinching the series 3-0 at Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium. Sanju Samson's explosive 111 off 47 balls stood out, supported by Suryakumar Yadav's 75 off 35 balls. Captain Yadav emphasized team flexibility and praised both batsmen and bowlers for their commendable performances.
title: 'No one is bigger than team': Surya recalls Gambhir's words

description: Leaders of Nihon Hidankyo warn of an increasing nuclear war threat and call for complete nuclear disarmament. Shigemitsu Tanaka, bomb survivor, emphasizes the deteriorating global situation amid tensions. Their plea follows receiving the Nobel Peace Prize, recognizing their anti-nuclear efforts, and is highlighted by recent statements from Russian President Vladimir Putin on nuclear options.
title: Nobel Peace prize winners, atomic bomb survivors, warn of nuclear threat

description: New Zealand's win over Sri Lanka narrows down the semi-finals prospects in Group A. With two matches left, India faces defending champions Australia, and Pakistan takes on New Zealand. India's higher net run rate offers an edge, but the outcomes of these matches will determine the final two teams advancing alongside Australia.
title: What India must do to qualify for T20 WC semis

description: Karnataka Deputy CM D K Shivakumar announced that all institutional buildings in Bengaluru must hoist the Kannada flag on Rajyotsava, Nov 1, to mark 50 years since Mysore was renamed Karnataka. He emphasized the importance of Kannada and cautioned against forcibly imposing the rule.
title: Hoist Kannada flag on Nov 1, Karnataka tells companies, factories, institutions

description: Ahead of the Shanghai Cooperation Organisation summit, Pakistan gears up to secure Islamabad amid recent militant attacks and political unrest. Authorities enforce strict measures, including troop deployment and a ban on protests. Key attendees include officials from China, India, and Russia. The summit will focus on trade, humanitarian, and cultural issues, despite Pakistan's escalating domestic tensions.
title: Pakistan prepares for SCO Summit amidst security concerns

description: Sanju Samson, after a spell of poor form, made a grand comeback by scoring a rapid century in the T20I series against Bangladesh. Reflecting on his journey, he credited his resilience and the unwavering support from the Indian team for his success, which led to India's 3-0 series victory. Reflecting on his recent struggles, the 29-year-old admitted he had doubts about receiving another chance after his two ducks in Sri Lanka.
title: Sanju Samson reveals comeback story after 'two ducks'

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu expressed his condolences on Saturday for the passing of Ratan Tata, former chairperson of the Tata Group. Describing Tata as "a proud son of India and a champion of the friendship between our two countries," Netanyahu urged Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi to convey his sympathies to Tata's family in a post on X.
title: 'Champion of friendship ... ': Netanyahu pays tribute to Ratan Tata

description: Ohio Senator JD Vance expressed his feelings about taking his Hindu-raised wife, Usha, to Catholic Mass regularly, admitting she didn't expect it but supported his spiritual journey. Usha encouraged him, believing it was beneficial for him. Their wedding included both Christian and Hindu ceremonies, reflecting their diverse backgrounds and her unwavering support.
title: 'She didn't sign up for this': Vance on 'dragging' Hindu wife Usha to Church

description: Replacing ultra-processed foods with minimally processed or processed alternatives can reduce diabetes risk, according to a Lancet study. The study, involving over three lakh people, found a 17% increased diabetes incidence for every 10% rise in ultra-processed food intake. Certain foods like breads and cereals were linked to lower risk, while snacks and sugary beverages increased it.
title: Replacing ultra-processed foods in diet cuts risk of diabetes, suggests study

description: IPS officer M Chandrasekhar has lodged a complaint accusing Union minister H D Kumaraswamy and his son, Nikhil, of intimidation and obstructing a probe into a 2007 mining scam. Chandrasekhar alleges verbal threats and false bribery charges, while Kumaraswamy denies any wrongdoing.
title: Mining scam: SIT chief goes to cops over H D Kumaraswamy's ‘threats’

description: Karnataka Deputy CM D K Shivakumar announced that all institutional buildings in Bengaluru must hoist the Kannada flag on Rajyotsava, Nov 1, to mark 50 years since Mysore was renamed Karnataka. He emphasized the importance of Kannada and cautioned against forcibly imposing the rule.
title: Hoist Kannada flag on Nov 1, Karnataka tells comapniess, factories, institutions

description: Plans are being made to extend the PM Gati Shakti scheme internationally, with engagements in progress with several neighboring countries. The scheme, which has integrated numerous ministries and data layers for efficient infrastructure planning, aims to grant access to non-sensitive planning data to non-government players. Currently, 208 projects worth over Rs 15 lakh crore are awaiting approval.
title: PM Gati Shakti set to go global, talks on with several countries

description: Two inmates, including a convicted murderer and an undertrial suspect, exploited a distraction during a Ramlila performance to escape from Haridwar District Jail. Despite authorities' immediate response, the prisoners remain untraceable, leading to a probe and suspension of six jail staffers for negligence.
title: 2 flee Uttarakhand jail. Did they escape as Ramlila ‘vanars’ looking for Sita?

description: Former Delhi University professor GN Saibaba passed away at age 57 due to post-surgery complications following gallstone removal. Recently acquitted of Maoist links by the Bombay High Court, Saibaba spent over seven years in prison, which severely affected his health. He was known for his activism and dedication to various social movements.
title: G N Saibaba, DU professor cleared of Naxal links after 10-year ordeal, dies

description: Indian spinner Ravi Bishnoi's 3/30 spell led India's 133-run victory over Bangladesh, securing a 3-0 series sweep in Hyderabad. At 24, Bishnoi is the youngest Indian to reach 50 T20I wickets. He emphasized continuous improvement and valued team competition as motivational factors. Bishnoi also touched on his recent break, saying, "I had a few days off and tried to make the most of that time to recharge and improve."
title: India spinner Ravi Bishnoi becomes youngest to ...

description: NIA is probing potential sabotage in a train collision at Kavarapettai station near Chennai that injured eight and overturned 12 coaches. Despite receiving a green signal, the Mysuru-Darbhanga Bagmati Express switched to a loop line, crashing into a parked goods train. Suspicious tampering with signal components raises concerns, and officials will investigate next week.
title: NIA probes sabotage angle in train accident near Chennai

description: Sanju Samson's stellar 111 off 47 balls, featuring eight sixes and 11 fours, secured India's highest-ever T20I score of 297/6 against Bangladesh. His century, the second-fastest by an Indian in T20I history, contributed to India's 133-run victory and 3-0 series sweep. Samson emphasized continuous improvement and the vital support from team leadership.
title: 'I have failed a lot': Sanju Samson opens up on personal struggles

description: Baba Siddique, a former Maharashtra MLA and NCP member, was shot dead outside his son's office in Bandra by three assailants. Two attackers were captured but one remains at large. The police are probing a possible SRA dispute or gang involvement.
title: NCP’s Baba Siddique shot dead outside his MLA son’s office, 2 held

description: Six Delhi policemen disguised themselves as labourers to arrest Raju Banarsi, a fugitive wanted for a decade-old murder over a property dispute. Banarsi, who had changed his identity and worked as a truck driver in the Chhattisgarh-Jharkhand border area, was ultimately captured following careful surveillance and infiltration by the officers.
title: Delhi cops disguised as labourers arrest fugitive murder accused in dense forest

description: A driverless car engulfed in flames descended an elevated road in Jaipur, colliding with a parked bike before halting at a divider. No injuries were reported. The incident occurred after Jitendra Jangid stepped out to investigate smoke from the car's engine, which then caught fire.
title: Panic grips Jaipur as burning car sans driver speeds through traffic

description: The LG’s secretariat accused AAP of misleading people by subverting norms in the bungalow allotment to CM Atishi. They claimed that the residence was handed over improperly and not legally sanctioned by MCD. AAP refuted these accusations, asserting they are focusing on restoring halted projects.
title: Delhi CM bungalow row: LG secretariat, CMO squabble over ‘abuse’
